```

## Context

Working directory: `/Users/rohanpuri/Desktop/Projects/Discord-Bot`. Tasks 1-3 complete. `utils/filter.js` exports `filterResults(results)` where `results` is an array of objects with `title` and `webpage_url` fields — exactly what yt-dlp's `--dump-json` output provides.

Key details:
- yt-dlp is installed at `/opt/homebrew/bin/yt-dlp`
- The `ytsearch5:` prefix tells yt-dlp to search YouTube and return up to 5 results
- `--dump-json` outputs one JSON object per line (each a video with title, webpage_url, uploader, etc.)
- `execFileAsync` is used (not execSync) to avoid blocking the Node.js event loop
- `execFile` with array args is safe — no shell injection risk even with artist name from user
- Return value: first filtered result object (has .title and .webpage_url), or null if nothing passes filter

## Your Job

